# Admin portal — keep the roadmap current

Any time you build, change, or extend the Admin portal, you MUST update
[docs/ADMIN_PORTAL_ROADMAP.md](../../docs/ADMIN_PORTAL_ROADMAP.md) in the same change. This doc is the canonical, durable record of what exists and why.

Update it when you:
- add/alter an admin-managed table or column → reflect it in the data-model section.
- add/change an `/api/admin/*` endpoint or its permission guard → reflect it in the backend surface.
- add/change an admin tab or `Admin*` component → reflect it in the frontend tab table.
- add a new permission key or role, or change RBAC enforcement (legacy map vs platform `requirePermission`) → update the auth/RBAC + decisions sections.
- make a non-obvious architectural decision (scheduling, discounts, sessions, theming) → add it to the "architecture & key decisions" section with the rationale ("why"), since this doc preserves intent for posterity.
- close or discover a rough edge → update "Known gaps".

Keep edits accurate and grounded in real code (cite file paths, table/column, endpoint names, permission keys). Do not let the doc drift from reality.
